The paper is about investigating the effectiveness of different stop words lists for Arabic Information Retrieval, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The study also involves the use of statistical language modelling, which is a common technique in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves comparing the performance of different weighting schemes, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Deep Learning (cs.DL).
